B. Data Preprocessing and Missing Value Imputation

Code 
def compute_correlation(data):
    corrmat = data.corr().abs()
    top_corr_features = corrmat.index
    return corrmat


def reducing_dimension(cor_matrix, th=0.7):
    upper_tri = cor_matrix.where(np.triu(np.ones(cor_matrix.shape), k=1).astype(np.bool))
    to_drop = [column for column in upper_tri.columns if any(upper_tri[column] > th)]
    return to_drop


corrmat_data = compute_correlation(train_df)
feature_to_drop = reducing_dimension(corrmat_data, th=0.7)
final_train_df = train_df.drop(columns=feature_to_drop)
final_test_df = test_df.drop(columns=feature_to_drop)
import re

final_train_df = final_train_df.rename(columns=lambda x: re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9_]+', '', x))
final_test_df = final_test_df.rename(columns=lambda x: re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9_]+', '', x))
for column in list(final_train_df.columns[final_train_df.isnull().sum() > 0]):
    mean_val = final_train_df[column].mean()
    final_train_df[column].fillna(mean_val, inplace=True)
    final_test_df[column].fillna(mean_val, inplace=True)

# define function to plot roc curve
def plot_roc_curve(_fpr, _tpr, label=None):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.title('ROC Curve')
    plt.plot(_fpr, _tpr, linewidth=2, label=label)
    plt.plot(_fpr, _tpr, 'o')
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1])
    plt.axis([-0.005, 1, 0, 1.005])
    plt.xticks(np.arange(0, 1, 0.05), rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate (Recall)")
    if label is not None:
        plt.legend(loc='best')
        plt.legend()


# define function to plot precision recall curve
def plot_precision_recall_vs_threshold(precisions, recalls, _thresholds):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.title("Precision and Recall vs Decision Threshold")
    plt.plot(_thresholds, precisions[:-1], label="Precision")
    plt.plot(_thresholds, recalls[:-1], label="Recall")
    plt.plot(_thresholds, precisions[:-1], "o")
    plt.plot(_thresholds, recalls[:-1], "o")
    plt.ylabel("Score")
    plt.xlabel("Decision Threshold")
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.legend()

B. Optimizing the decision threshold probability for Bagging

Code 
cross_val_ypred = cross_val_predict(random_search_Bagging.best_estimator_,
                                    X_train,
                                    y_train, cv=StratifiedKFold(3), method='predict_proba')
Code 
fpr, tpr, auc_thresholds = roc_curve(y_train, cross_val_ypred[:, 1])

fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_train, cross_val_ypred[:, 1])
AUC = auc(fpr, tpr)
plot_roc_curve(fpr, tpr, label="AUC=" + str(AUC))
p, r, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_train, cross_val_ypred[:, 1])
plot_precision_recall_vs_threshold(p, r, thresholds)

Code 
hyperparam_vals = np.arange(0, 1.01, 0.01)
beta_iter = []

for threshold_prob in hyperparam_vals:
    predicted_class = cross_val_ypred[:, 1] > threshold_prob
    predicted_class = predicted_class.astype(int)

    #Computing F1
    p = precision_score(y_train, predicted_class)
    r = recall_score(y_train, predicted_class)
    beta = 2 * p * r / (p + r)
    beta_iter.append(beta)
sns.scatterplot(x=hyperparam_vals, y=beta_iter)
plt.xlabel('Decision threshold probability')
plt.ylabel('Average 3-fold CV F1')
hyperparam_vals[beta_iter.index(max(beta_iter))]
0.12

Code 
desired_threshold = hyperparam_vals[beta_iter.index(max(beta_iter))]
print(desired_threshold)
y_pred_prob = random_search_Bagging.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
y_pred = y_pred_prob > desired_threshold
y_pred = y_pred.astype(int)
print("Bagging Accuracy: ", accuracy_score(y_pred, y_test))
print("Bagging Precision: ", precision_score(y_test, y_pred))
print("Bagging Recall: ", recall_score(y_test, y_pred))

B. Optimizing Decision Threshold

Code 
cross_val_ypred = cross_val_predict(random_search_RF.best_estimator_,
                                    X_train,
                                    y_train, cv=5, method='predict_proba', n_jobs=-1)
Code 
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_train, cross_val_ypred[:, 1])
AUC = auc(fpr, tpr)
plot_roc_curve(fpr, tpr, label="AUC=" + str(AUC))
p, r, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_train, cross_val_ypred[:, 1])
plot_precision_recall_vs_threshold(p, r, thresholds)

Code 
hyperparam_vals = np.arange(0, 1.01, 0.01)
beta_iter = []

for threshold_prob in hyperparam_vals:
    predicted_class = cross_val_ypred[:, 1] > threshold_prob
    predicted_class = predicted_class.astype(int)
    #Computing F1
    p = precision_score(y_train, predicted_class)
    r = recall_score(y_train, predicted_class)
    beta = 2 * p * r / (p + r)
    beta_iter.append(beta)
sns.scatterplot(x=hyperparam_vals, y=beta_iter)
plt.xlabel('Decision threshold probability')
plt.ylabel('Average 3-fold CV F1')
hyperparam_vals[beta_iter.index(max(beta_iter))]
0.5

Code 
desired_threshold = hyperparam_vals[beta_iter.index(max(beta_iter))]
print(f"Optimal decision threshold: {desired_threshold}")
y_pred_prob = random_search_RF.best_estimator_.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
y_pred = y_pred_prob > desired_threshold
y_pred = y_pred.astype(int)
